HEADWORD: Uropygial
<hw>U`ro*pyg"i*al</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Uropygium</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Anat.)</fld> <def>Of or pertaining to
the uropygium, or prominence at the base of the tail feathers, in
birds.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Uropygial gland</b></col>, <cd>a peculiar sebaceous gland
at the base of the tail feathers in most birds. It secretes an oily
fluid which is spread over the feathers by preening.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Uropygium</ent>⟦br⟧
